Property.name: Description
Property.value: The unit can be used to indicate a quantitity without a specific Unit of Measure (like Pieces)

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The metre is the basic unit of length. It is the distance light travels, in a vacuum, in 1/299792458th of a second.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kilogram is the basic unit of mass. It is the mass of an international prototype in the form of a platinum-iridium cylinder kept at Sevres in France.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The second is the basic unit of time. It is the length of time taken for 9192631770 periods of vibration of the caesium-133 atom to occur.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The ampere is the basic unit of electric current. It is that current which produces a specified force between two parallel wires which are 1 metre apart in a vacuum.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The kelvin is the basic unit of temperature. It is 1/273.16th of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The mole is the basic unit of substance. It is the amount of substance that contains as many elementary units as there are atoms in 0.012 kg of carbon-12.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The candela is the basic unit of luminous intensity. It is the intensity of a source of light of a specified frequency, which gives a specified amount of power in a given direction.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The hertz is the SI unit of the frequency of a periodic phenomenon. One hertz indicates that 1 cycle of the phenomenon occurs every second. For most work much higher frequencies are needed such as the kilohertz [kHz] and megahertz [MHz].

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The newton is the SI unit of force. One newton is the force required to give a mass of 1 kilogram an acceleration of 1 metre per second per second.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The joule is the SI unit of work or energy. One joule is the amount of work done when an applied force of 1 newton moves through a distance of 1 metre in the direction of the force.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The watt is used to measure power or the rate of doing work. One watt is a power of 1 joule per second.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The volt is the SI unit of electric potential. One volt is the difference of potential between two points of an electical conductor when a current of 1 ampere flowing between those points dissipates a power of 1 watt.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The pascal is the SI unit of pressure. One pascal is the pressure generated by a force of 1 newton acting on an area of 1 square metre. It is a rather small unit as defined and is more often used as a kilopascal [kPa].

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The farad is the SI unit of the capacitance of an electrical system, that is, its capacity to store electricity. It is a rather large unit as defined and is more often used as a microfarad.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The ohm is the SI unit of resistance of an electrical conductor. Its symbol, is the capital Greek letter omega.

Property.name: Description
Property.value: The pH of a solution is defined to be the negative logarithm of the concentration, measured in moles per liter. This unit is inverted in the sense that lower pH readings correspond to greater acidity, and therefore more hydrogen ions.
